\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 5. FAQs About White Paper Writing\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0\cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 What is a White Paper?: A white paper is a comprehensive report designed to inform the reader about a particular topic, presenting a problem and providing a solution.\
\ls4\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 How Long Should It Be?: The length can vary, but most white papers are between 6-20 pages. The key is to ensure all necessary information is covered without unnecessary fluff.\
\ls4\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Who Reads Them?: Typically, white papers target professionals in a particular field or industry, especially decision-makers.\
